Package: timecop
Title: Estimation of Latent Gaussian VAR Models for Discrete-Valued Time Series
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:c(
    person("Christopher", "Crawford", , "cmcrawford4792@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Younghoon", "Kim", role = "aut"),
    person("Zachary","Fisher", email = "fish.zachary@gmail.com", role = c("ctb")),
    person("Vladas", "Pipiras", role = "ctb"),
    person("Duker", "Marie", role = "ctb")
    )
Description: Estimates latent Gaussian vector autoregressive (VAR) models for
    discrete-valued multivariate time series. Supports Bernoulli, Poisson, and
    Gaussian marginal distributions through a latent variable approach using
    Hermite polynomial expansion. Estimation is performed via a method-of-moments
    Yule-Walker procedure with standard errors derived from the long-run variance
    of the estimating equations. Currently supports VAR order p=1.
